The paper focuses on a tool for detecting and reporting crashes in Android applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) categories. The tool uses systematic input generation and static and dynamic analyses, which are techniques commonly used in systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the usability of the tool's reports, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
